We now allows extension writer to contribute menu items. The next logical step is to allow user to configure their menus - this is analog to the keybindings-story. One idea is to have a `menus.json` file which defines your menus:

``` json
{
  "editor/context": [
  {
    "command": "my command",
    "when": "editorHasSelection"
  },
  {
   // more..
  }
  ],
 "explorer/context": [
   // more ...
  ]
}
```

Reproduces also in stable 1.3.1. 

Have JS/TS code like this:

```
var foo = 3;
console.log(foo);
```

Ctrl+hover over foo and notice you are not seeing the source preview in the hover. However if I debug this, I see that the decoration receives the line content in https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/blob/master/src/vs/editor/contrib/goToDeclaration/browser/goToDeclaration.ts#L393

